<br>
On the coffee thing, there are other harmful things in coffee besides caffeine. And I would venture to say that most active LDS are pretty strict about avoiding any coffee products.  Like I dont even eat mocha flavored ice cream because it uses real coffee to flavor it.<br>
<br>
In Costa Rica there was this burnt corn drink that everyone told me tasted just like coffee, I would probably use a substitute like that in a recipe that called for coffee. (That is if I could find it here -which I havent --and acutally liked the taste of it which I dont.)<br>
<br>
Another reason they probably dont want to have it in the chili is that  keeping the Word of Wisdom is part of the requirements to be a temple recommend holder.  Any intentional consumption of coffee, would be breaking that commandment.<br>
<br>
What about using a grain beverage similar in taste to coffee, and Odouls, would your parents be opposed to that?( I think something like that is a personal choice/preference)<br>
<br>
Hope it is a fun party!! - Shirene<br>
